Two-dimensional echocardiographic recognition of aortic valve ring abscess. 2D-echocardiography was performed in 42 consecutive patients with suspected aortic endocarditis who subsequently underwent surgery. On surgery, 12 patients had perivalvular aortic abscesses: in the posterior part of the ring (7) with extension to the aorto-mitral fibrous trigone or pseudo-aneurysm of the aortic wall in the anterior part of the ring (3), with extension toward the interventricular septum